  "primaryContentSections" : [
    {
      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "Overview",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Use ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "https:\/\/daringfireball.net\/projects\/markdown\/syntax",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", a",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "lightweight markup language, to give structure and style to your documentation.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "DocC includes a custom dialect of Markdown, documentation markup, which",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "extends Markdown’s syntax to include features like symbol linking, improved",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "image support, term lists, and asides.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "To ensure consistent structure and styling, use DocC’s documentation markup for",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "all of the documentation you write.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Add-a-Page-Title-and-Section-Headers",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Add a Page Title and Section Headers",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "To add a page title, precede the text you want to use with a hash (",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "#",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ") and a",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "space. For the page title of an article or API collection, use plain text only.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "# Getting Started with Sloths"
          ],
          "syntax" : "markdown",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "content" : [
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "Page titles must be the first line of content in a documentation",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : " ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : "file. One or more empty lines can precede the page title.",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name" : "Important",
          "style" : "important",
          "type" : "aside"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "For the page title of a landing page, enter a symbol link by wrapping the framework’s",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "module name within a set of double backticks (``).",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "# ``SlothCreator``"
          ],
          "syntax" : "markdown",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "For a documentation extension file, enter a symbol link by wrapping the path to the symbol",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "within double backticks (``). The path may start with the framework’s module name",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "or with the name of a top-level symbol in the module.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The following example shows a documentation extension link starting with a framework module name:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "# ``SlothCreator\/CareSchedule\/Event``"
          ],
          "syntax" : "markdown",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The following example shows a documentation extension link to the same symbol starting with a top-level symbol name:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "# ``CareSchedule\/Event``"
          ],
          "syntax" : "markdown",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Augment every page title with a short and concise single-sentence abstract or",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "summary that provides additional information about the content. Add the summary",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "using a new paragraph directly below the page title.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "# Getting Started with Sloths",
            "",
            "Create a sloth and assign personality traits and abilities."
          ],
          "syntax" : "markdown",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "To add a header for an Overview or a Discussion section, use a double hash",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "(",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "##",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ") and a space, and then include either term in plain text.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "## Overview"
          ],
          "syntax" : "markdown",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "For all other section headers, use a triple hash (",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "###",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ") and a space, and then",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "add the title of the header in plain text.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "### Create a Sloth"
          ],
          "syntax" : "markdown",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Use this type of section header in framework landing pages, top-level pages,",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "articles, and occasionally in symbol reference pages where you need to",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "provide more detail.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Format-Text-in-Bold-Italics-and-Code-Voice",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Format Text in Bold, Italics, and Code Voice",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "DocC provides three ways to format the text in your documentation. You can",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "apply bold or italic styling, or you can use code voice, which renders the",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "specified text in a monospace font.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "To add bold styling, wrap the text in a pair of double asterisks (",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "**",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ").",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Alternatively, use double underscores (",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "__",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ").",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The following example uses bold styling for the names of the sloths:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "**Super Sloth**: Likes to eat sticks.",
            "__Silly Sloth__: Prefers twigs for breakfast."
          ],
          "syntax" : "markdown",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Use italicized text to introduce new or alternative terms to the reader. To add",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "italic styling, wrap the text in a set of single underscores (",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "_",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ") or single",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "asterisks (",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "*",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ").",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The following example uses italics for the words ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "metabolism",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text" : " and ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "habitat",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text" : ":",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "A sloth's _metabolism_ is highly dependent on its *habitat*."
          ],
          "syntax" : "markdown",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Use code voice to refer to symbols inline, or to include short code fragments,",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "such as class names or method signatures.  To add code voice, wrap the text in",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "a set of backticks (`).",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "In the following example, DocC renders the words ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "ice",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "fire",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "wind",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", and",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "lightning",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text" : " in a monospace font:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "If your sloth possesses one of the special powers: `ice`, `fire`,",
            "`wind`, or `lightning`."
