          "name" : "Note",
          "style" : "note",
          "type" : "aside"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Add-Code-Listings",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Add Code Listings",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "DocC includes support for code listings, or fenced code blocks, which allow you",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "to go beyond the basic declaration sections you find in symbol reference pages,",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "and to provide more complete code examples for adopters of your framework. You can",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "include code listings in your in-source symbol documentation, in extension",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "files, and in articles and tutorials.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "To create a code listing, start a new paragraph and add three backticks",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "(```). Then, directly following the backticks, add the name of the",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "programming language in lowercase text. Add one or more lines of code, and then",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "add a new line and terminate the code listing by adding another three backticks:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "```swift",
            "struct Sightseeing: Activity {",
            "    func perform(with sloth: inout Sloth) -> Speed {",
            "        sloth.energyLevel -= 10",
            "        return .slow",
            "    }",
            "}",
            "```"
          ],
          "syntax" : "markdown",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "content" : [
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "When formatting your code listing, use spaces to indent lines",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : " ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : "instead of tabs so that DocC preserves the indentation when compiling your",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : " ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : "documentation.",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name" : "Important",
          "style" : "important",
          "type" : "aside"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "DocC uses the programming language you specify to apply the correct syntax",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "color formatting. For the example above, DocC generates the following:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "struct Sightseeing: Activity {",
            "    func perform(with sloth: inout Sloth) -> Speed {",
            "        sloth.energyLevel -= 10",
            "        return .slow",
